<p>I was loving it, right up until presented to SCP-682 and Agent went into a 'chronic depression' after a week of coma.<br />
Chronic Depression is characterized by a long-term (two years or more) depressed mood. As it happens, chronic depression is actually less severe.<br />
For the sake of science, please edit that bit into something along the lines of.. When awoke from the coma, he was diagnosed with Major Depressive Episode which later on evolved into a Chronic Depression.</p>
<p>I can understand the need to present this scp to other scps, but I think it would be nice if presented to some other random seemingly normal objects.. and maybe find something really interesting about them?</p>

